A REST API (Representational State Transfer Application Programming Interface) is an interface that allows different applications to communicate with each other over the internet. REST APIs use HTTP (Hypertext Transfer Protocol) to send and receive data. REST APIs are designed to be simple, scalable, and easy to use.

Here is an example of a simple REST API using Flask:

```python
from flask import Flask, jsonify

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/users/<int:user_id>', methods=['GET'])
def get_user(user_id):
    # retrieve user data from database
    user = {'id': user_id, 'name': 'John Doe'}
    return jsonify(user)

@app.route('/users/<int:user_id>', methods=['POST'])
def create_user(user_id):
    # create user data in database
    user = {'id': user_id, 'name': 'Jane Doe'}
    return jsonify(user)

if __name__ == '__main__':
